You would like to change the byte- to- inode ratio on a new filesystem in order to preventinode exhaustion. Which option to mke2fs accomplishes this task?
A)  - b
B)  - r
C)  - i
D)  - u
C
C. The - i option sets the byte- to- inode ratio. The - b option sets the block size, - r sets thefilesystem revision, and there is no - u option for mke2fs.
